rtone2003/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caspertone2003/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caspertone2003/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-08-10T01:25:25Z","updated_at":"2020-08-10T01:25:25Z","body":"Not a bad critic to an application I love but an enhancement suggestion.\r\nSorry for piggy-backing the thread.\r\n===================================================\r\nI suffered this situation and come back to github to search for help... While I already found how to renew the token using config , as well explained here https://forum.rclone.org/t/coming-back-to-rclone-after-a-year-now-nothing-works/6573/2\r\n\r\nI wonder...\r\nAll explained there, could not be automated? I mean, when this error is detected, by offering the user the refresh of the token? Could rclone avoid the user to run config, select the remote, press enter over ten (?) times until the following question pops up:\r\n\r\nAlready have a token - refresh?\r\ny) Yes\r\nn) No\r\ny/n>\r\n\r\nSo, I would like to propose the following enhancement: to just open a message to the user with the message:\r\n\"GDrive authentication token seems to have expired; would you like to obtain a new one? y/n?\"\r\n\r\nThat would be much way user friendly than putting a more clear error message...\r\n\r\nTIA\r\nCT","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/671129150/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"caspertone2003","id":4682903,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ2ODI5MDM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4682903?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/caspertone2003","html_url":"https://github.com/caspertone2003","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caspertone2003/follo